    "chemicalDescription": [
      "r-(Oligopeptide-126 sh-Oligopeptide-1 sh-Polypeptide-124 sh-Polypeptide-2) is a single chain fusion peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the genes encoding for Oligopeptide-126 , sh-Oligopeptide-1 , sh-Polypeptide-124 and sh-Polypeptide-2. The fusion peptide contains 193 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
